sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
This action creates First Advantage Screening Orders.

Inputs:

  • Candidate ID - The ID of the candidate for whom the screening order is to be created.
  • Package ID - The ID of the chosen screening package.
  • Account ID - ID of the account.
  • Two Step - Flag to create 1-step or 2-step order.
  • Notification URL - A ServiceNow callback URL for First Advantage status notifications.
  • Client References - A ServiceNow case or request ID.
  • User Defined Fields - User defined fields.
  • Quote Backs Quoteback reference for clients.
    • Name - Quoteback name
    • Value - Quoteback value
  • Order As - Ordering Account details.
    • Account ID - Requested account ID
    • User ID - Requested user ID
    • Email - Requested email ID
  • Locale - Locale information.
    • Language Code - Language code (e.g. en)
    • Country Code - Country code
  • Position Applied For - Name of the position to apply.
  • Position Locations - Details of the position.
    • City - Position in the city.
    • State - Position in the state.
    • Country - Position in the country.
  • Add Ons - Add-on indicator for screening components.
    • Type - Type code for screening components.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "Success" if the request succeeds or "Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".
  • Order ID - Order ID of the order that is created.

Error Messages:

  • The Account ID or User ID under Order As is invalid.
  • Provided Package ID is invalid.
  • Either Candidate ID or Package ID appear to be empty.
  • Provided value for one of the inputs is invalid.
  • The provided language is not supported or the country code doesnot corresponds to the provided language code.
  • Provided Candidate ID is invalid or not found.

To use this action, the corresponding First Advantage connection and credential must be created and associated with the First Advantage Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
